headline: Ticket reseller StubHub's IPO 20 times oversubscribed, source says
summary: (Reuters) -Ticket reseller StubHub, which delayed its U.S. listing in April amid market volatility, has drawn over 20 times as many orders for its planned initial public offering as there are available shares, a source familiar with the matter said on Friday.  The outsized demand for the IPO, which is set to price shares on Tuesday, reflects pent-up investor appetite for tech-heavy consumer platforms.  StubHub did not immediately respond to Reuters' request for comment.
